Question: How to get the current time in milliseconds in Java?: <<<api>>>: System.currentTimeMillis
<<<code>>>: long currentTimeMillis = System.currentTimeMillis();
<<<explanation>>>: The currentTimeMillis() method of the System class returns the current time in milliseconds.
Question: How to get the current time in nanoseconds in Java?: <<<api>>>: System.nanoTime
<<<code>>>: long nanoTime = System.nanoTime();
<<<explanation>>>: The nanoTime() method of the System class returns the current value of the most precise available system timer, in nanoseconds.
Question: How to get the current time in seconds in Java?: <<<api>>>: System.currentTimeMillis
<<<code>>>: long currentTimeMillis = System.currentTimeMillis();
long currentTimeSeconds = currentTimeMillis / 1000;
<<<explanation>>>: The currentTimeMillis() method of the System class returns the current time in milliseconds. Divide by 1000 to get the current time in seconds.
Question: How to get the current time in minutes in Java?: <<<api>>>: System.currentTimeMillis
<<<code>>>: long currentTimeMillis = System.currentTimeMillis();
long currentTimeMinutes = currentTimeMillis / 1000 / 60;
<<<explanation>>>: The currentTimeMillis() method of the System class returns the current time in milliseconds. Divide by 1000 to get the current time in seconds. Divide by 60 to get the current time in minutes.
Question: How to get the current time in hours in Java?: <<<api>>>: System.currentTimeMillis
